<AbstractNarration>0000454&lt;br/&gt;Brodsky&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Pulsating behavior in volcanic systems is ubiquitous and physically significant for understanding the force balance of eruptive processes.  The PI will carry out a systematic study of oscillations over a wide range of frequencies using the analytical and numerical tools of fluid mechanics.  The goal is to formulate a set of criteria by which specific mechanisms or classes of mechanisms can be associated with documented observations.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
